<subSubSection id="09AB84DA42118949FF755DCEFB85C75C" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="410ED75142118949FF755DCEFE91C6D7" blockId="22.[227,341,1665,1691]" box="[227,341,1665,1691]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="1A46603D42118949FF755DCEFE91C6D7" bold="true" box="[227,341,1665,1691]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis id="73C50B4342118949FF755DCEFE91C6D7" bold="true" box="[227,341,1665,1691]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="410ED75142118949FF755DFFFB85C75C" blockId="22.[227,1437,1711,1808]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName id="86B1ACD242118949FF755DFFFE95C685" authorityName="Korn" authorityYear="2001" box="[227,337,1712,1737]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Taouzitidae" genus="Taouzites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73C50B4342118949FF755DFFFE95C685" box="[227,337,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">Taouzites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents the morphological end member of an evolutionary series in the Givetian, which, starting from simple gephuroceratids, is characterised by a flattening of the conch with a sharpening venter and simultaneous proliferation of the umbilical lobes (
<bibRefCitation id="2520AAA042118949FC265DB9FBF0C75C" author="Korn D." box="[944,1076,1782,1808]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" pagination="193 - 215" refId="ref18127" refString="Korn D. 2001. Morphometric evolution and phylogeny of Palaeozoic ammonoids. Early and Middle Devonian. Acta Geologica Polonica 51: 193 - 215." type="journal article" year="2001">Korn 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
